## 📘 07 - Semantic Tags

Semantic tags improve HTML structure and accessibility.  
They give meaning to your content and help search engines & screen readers understand your page.

---

## 📂 Files Included

1. 01-header.html → Header section for page or section
2. 02-nav.html → Navigation menus
3. 03-section-article.html → Section with multiple articles
4. 04-footer.html → Footer section
5. 05-combined-layout.html → Full page example combining all semantic tags

---

## 🔹 Basic Semantic Tags
- `<header>` → Introductory content of a page or section
- `<nav>` → Navigation links
- `<section>` → Thematic grouping of content
- `<article>` → Independent content piece
- `<footer>` → Page or section footer

---

## 🔹 Advanced Usage Tips
- Combine tags for full page layout
- Use `<article>` inside `<section>` for grouped content
- Use `<footer>` for copyright, links, or contact info
- Semantic tags improve SEO and accessibility

Each file explains one concept clearly from beginner to advanced usage.
